The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                The doctor father of a 17-year-old girl who died of drug overdose on October 24 has accused a young doctor, who lives next door, of abetting her suicide. A case of unnatural death was started on Wednesday. The girl, a resident of Kalikapur, died in a private hospital on EM Bypass. Her father M.K. Sarkar alleged that their neighbour had verbally asked her to take the medicines that killed her. The girl studied in a coaching centre that the young doctor ran in his home. According to police, the girl had fallen for her neighbour and was heartbroken after his marriage was fixed elsewhere.     A Trinamul Congress demonstration, led by Mamata Banerjee, in Metro channel on Thursday caused severe traffic snarls on roads leading to Esplanade. Motorists were stranded on Park Street flyover, SN Banerjee Road, RR Avenue and Government Place (East). The demonstration was organised to protest attacks on Trinamul supporters in Singur.     Rakesh Das, a 25-year-old building materials supplier, was arrested on Thursday for allegedly threatening the manager of a construction project in Tangra. Police said Das had demanded that he be given the contract of supplying sand to the civic body project that was being executed by the company.    Santosh Haldar, 38, was arrested on Thursday in connection with three cases of snatching from passengers in taxi. The Sonarpur resident was picked up from his hideout at Kulpi.    Supporters of Lok Janashakti Party will demonstrate near the chief ministers residence on Friday morning to demand a CBI inquiry into the November 2 attack on Ram Vilas Paswan in Salboni.     A 15-year-old boy was arrested in the port area on Thursday for allegedly beating his neighbour with a bamboo stick during a cricket match.                                                                                                                                                                 
